  "texts": [
    "This approach is based on estimating the nearest neighbor.",
    "The new instances are categorized using a distance metric to measure similarity.",
    "The K in KNN stands for the number of nearest neighbors' data items.",
    "The main concept of the KNN model is that a new instance's prediction is formed by scanning the whole training set for comparable K neighbor examples and classifying them according to the class with the most occurrences.",
    "To discover a comparable situation, the Euclidean distance formula is employed."
